cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with face recognition using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with matching polarimetric thermal face photos against a gallery of visible faces, which involves multimedia data. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a novel Attribute-Guided Coupled Generative Adversarial Network (AGC-GAN) architecture which utilizes facial attributes to improve the thermal-to-visible face recognition performance. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with deep learning techniques for face recognition. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with matching faces against a gallery of visible faces, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
